'''Sergio Ramón Rochet Álvarez''' (born 23 March 1993) is an Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] of [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] and [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

==Club career==
Rochet started his career with [[Danubio F.C.|Danubio]] with whom he made no appearances.

===AZ Alkmaar===
In April 2014, he went to trial with Dutch club [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] as they wanted a goalkeeper to serve as backup for [[Esteban Alvarado]] after the departure of [[Erik Heijblok]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Uruguayaans talent wil naar Europa en hoopt op contract bij AZ Lees |date=16 April 2014 |url=https://www.soccernews.nl/news/246611/Uruguayaans_talent_wil_naar_Europa_en_hoopt_op_contract_bij_AZ|publisher=Soccernews|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref> On 19 May 2014, he underwent medicals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Uruguayaanse doelman ondergaat medische keuring bij AZ|date=19 May 2014 |url=https://www.soccernews.nl/news/252649/Uruguayaanse_doelman_ondergaat_medische_keuring_bij_AZ|publisher=Soccernews|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref> Finally on 24 May 2014, he was signed by AZ for a contract until 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=AZ haalt doelman Rochet naar Alkmaar|url=http://www.az.nl/nieuws/az-haalt-doelman-rochet-naar-alkmaar/1|publisher=AZ|access-date=10 October 2014|archive-date=28 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728155510/http://www.az.nl/nieuws/az-haalt-doelman-rochet-naar-alkmaar/1|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Rochet made his debut against [[FC Dordrecht]] after Alvarado was injured.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dordecht vs AZ|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/08/30/netherlands/eredivisie/bvo-fc-dordrecht/stichting-az/1690533/|website=Soccerway|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref>

===Internacional===
On 13 July 2023, [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] officially announced Rochet's signing until December 2026. The Brazilian club agreed to pay a [[United States dollar|US$]]1.6 million transfer fee to [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ge.globo.com/rs/futebol/times/internacional/noticia/2023/07/13/inter-anuncia-contratacao-do-goleiro-sergio-rochet.ghtml |title=Inter anuncia contratação do goleiro Sérgio Rochet |publisher=ge.globo |language=pt-BR |date=13 July 2023 |access-date=13 July 2023}}</ref> On 8 August 2023, he scored the winning penalty in the shootout against [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] in the [[2023 Copa Libertadores final stages|2023 Copa Libertadores round of 16]].

Rochet started the next year with an injured torso, meaning he'd only make his season debut on 25 March<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 March 2024 |title=Com volta de Rochet, Inter está escalado para enfrentar o Juventude |url=https://gauchazh.clicrbs.com.br/esportes/inter/noticia/2024/03/com-volta-de-rochet-inter-esta-escalado-para-enfrentar-o-juventude-clu7lm4ei00dp019ms337zxlz.html |access-date=30 December 2024 |website=GZH |language=pt}}</ref> as Inter got knocked out by [[Esporte Clube Juventude|Juventude]] in the [[2024 Campeonato Gaúcho|Campeonato Gaúcho]] semifinals. He'd retain his position as the starting goalkeeper, even as the club suffered the effects of the [[2024 Rio Grande do Sul floods|severe floods in Rio Grande do Sul]] in May: during this time, Rochet, as well as other players, participated in the relief efforts<ref>{{Cite web |last=Leite |first=Filipe Sodré, Mauri Dorneles, Pedro |title=Diego Costa, Mercado e Rochet ajudam vítimas de enchentes no Rio Grande do Sul |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/esportes/futebol/diego-costa-mercado-e-rochet-ajudam-vitimas-de-enchentes-no-rio-grande-do-sul/ |access-date=30 December 2024 |website=CNN Brasil |date=3 May 2024 |language=pt-BR}}</ref> while football had been postponed.

Rochet missed 12 Internacional matches between June and July while serving Uruguay during the [[2024 Copa América]] in the United States. He would make his team return on 16 July, during a loss to [[Rosario Central]] in the [[2024 Copa Sudamericana final stages|Sudamericana Play-Offs]]. Rochet would then play in 14 times during Internacional's memorable 16-match unbeaten run<ref>{{Cite web |title=16 jogos de invencibilidade! Relembre os jogos do Internacional desde a última derrota no Brasileirão - LANCE! |url=https://www.lance.com.br/galerias/16-jogos-de-invencibilidade-relembre-os-jogos-do-internacional-desde-a-ultima-derrota-no-brasileirao/ |access-date=30 December 2024 |website=LANCE! {{!}} Futebol, Fórmula 1, MMA e todos os esportes |language=pt-br}}</ref> under manager [[Roger Machado (footballer)|Roger Machado]], which saw the Colorado shoot up the [[2024 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Brasileirão]] table to 5th place finish. He made his 50th appearance for the club during a 2-2 draw away at [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]] on 5 October 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 October 2024 |title=Rochet faz 50 jogos pelo Inter e comenta sobre rivalidade com Corinthians: "Motivação extra" |url=https://ge.globo.com/rs/futebol/times/internacional/noticia/2024/10/04/rochet-faz-50-jogos-pelo-inter-e-comenta-sobre-rivalidade-com-corinthians-motivacao-extra.ghtml |access-date=30 December 2024 |website=ge |language=pt-br}}</ref>

==International career==
On 5 March 2021, Rochet was named in the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]]'s 35-man preliminary squad for [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifying matches]] against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=35 futbolistas reservados para enfrentar a Argentina y Bolivia por Eliminatorias|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/35-futbolistas-reservados-para-enfrentar-a-argentina-y-bolivia/|date=5 March 2021|access-date=7 March 2021}}</ref> However, [[CONMEBOL]] suspended those matches next day amid concern over the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CONMEBOL suspends March World Cup qualifiers after clubs' refusal to release players|date=6 March 2021 |url=https://www.espn.in/football/blog-fifa/story/4330687/conmebol-suspends-march-world-cup-qualifiers-after-clubs-refusal-to-release-players|access-date=7 March 2021}}</ref> He made his international debut on 27 January 2022 in a 1–0 win against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sergio Rochet: cómo se enteró de que iba a ser el arquero titular y la experiencia del debut|url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/ovacion/futbol/sergio-rochet-debut-seleccion-uruguaya-paraguay-eliminatorias.html|date=27 January 2022|access-date=28 January 2022}}</ref>

He was picked for the 2022 World Cup squad and started all three of Uruguay’s games, keeping a clean sheet in two of them. He also saved an [[André Ayew]] penalty against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]], but it was not enough for Uruguay to qualify for the round of 16.

On 31 May 2026, Rochet was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

